"What I cannot understand," said I, "is why they should have spared you when they found you lying
fainting in the garden. Perhaps the villain was softened by the woman's entreaties."

"I hardly think that likely. I never saw a more inexorable face in my life."

"Oh, we shall soon clear up all that," said Bradstreet. "Well, I have drawn my circle, and I only
wish I knew at what point upon it the folk that we are in search of are to be found."